25/08/2006
ANKARA.
Turkey -- The foreign ministry said late on Wednesday (23 August) that Turkey is undertaking monitoring and observation missions in southern Lebanon to assess the situation before making any decision regarding participation in an international peacekeeping force.
The ministry said that a group conducted comprehensive inspections of routes, locations, ports and command headquarters in the area last week.
(Zaman - 25/08/06;
NTV - 24/08/06)
